The paper discusses the use of algorithmic techniques to enhance the targeting and delivery of social and behavioral interventions, which falls under the category of social intervention. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also mentions decision making under uncertainty, which is a characteristic of cybernetics (cs.CY) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also discusses optimization algorithms, which can fall under machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses societal challenges, which can fall under the category of sociology (cs.SOC).
